        <abstract>
            <p>Australian Leguminosae problem: of 900 species not ten are common to southwest and southeast. No migration; hence either creation or variation.</p>
            <p>Himalayan thistles: graded intermediates between large and small English species, "shakes species to their foundations". Similarity of CD’s and his views on species.</p>
        </abstract>
